{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"493d19cc-fd3e-4f85-ba0c-401c3ebfa992","content":"Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`. As demonstrated:\n\n```csharp\nSpan<nint>  a = stackalloc nint[4];\nSpan<nuint> b = stackalloc nuint[3];\n```\n\nBoth work without issue. On this 64-bit system, `nint.MaxValue` is `9223372036854775807` (same as `long.MaxValue`) and `nuint.MaxValue` is `18446744073709551615` (same as `ulong.MaxValue`), confirming the native-sized integers are 8 bytes here.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9f2bb4a0-7bcf-485e-a09c-3bab4be16803","outputTokens":161,"requestId":"FE23:17D991:137844D:15D82B1:6A067012"},"id":"6fe9a2e3-3a1d-4324-a732-d5df7aadae44","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:00:06.938Z","parentId":"4a188397-a6b6-4ea5-bc19-e87ba9bff954"}
